Preconditions:
- The input matrix is not null.
- The input matrix is a valid 2D matrix with dimensions m x n.
- The integers in each row of the matrix are sorted in ascending order.
- The integers in each column of the matrix are sorted in ascending order.
- The target value is within the range of the integers in the matrix.

Postconditions:
- The method returns a boolean value indicating whether the target value was found in the matrix.
- If the target value is found in the matrix, the method returns true.
- If the target value is not found in the matrix, the method returns false.